{"body": "<p>If you are using <a href=\"https://github.com/apache/cordova-plugman\" rel=\"nofollow\">plugman</a> then</p>\n\n<pre><code>plugman install --platform android --project path/to/your/ionicapp/platforms/android --plugin /Path/to/your/cordova-plugin/MyDemo/\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>will install the plugin, read other options in project's <a href=\"https://github.com/apache/cordova-plugman#plugin-management\" rel=\"nofollow\">readme</a>.</p>\n", "tags": ["cordova", "plugins", "ionic"], "creation_date": 1474977431, "score": 1, "last_activity_date": 1474977431, "answer_id": 39724040, "is_accepted": false, "owner": {"user_id": 2341815, "reputation": 360, "user_type": "registered", "accept_rate": 53, "display_name": "Ruwanka Madhushan", "link": "http://stackoverflow.com/users/2341815/ruwanka-madhushan", "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/637ab45a810d6286bfa97ff77b505eaa?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG"}, "title": "How to add a local cordova plugin with Ionic?", "question_id": 30345035}